article.description: Alec Kobre scored 19 points and Jacob Lampkin's layup with 58 seconds left gave Pacific a 60-58 victory over Loyola Marymount on Saturday.
article.headline: Pacific edges Loyola Marymount 60-58
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Alec Kobre scored 19 points and Jacob Lampkin's layup with 58 seconds left gave Pacific a 60-58 victory over Loyola Marymount on Saturday. Lampkin scored underneath after a great baseline pass from Ray Bowles. Both teams exchanged misses before LMU's diminutive point guard, Brandon Brown, couldn't find an opening in the lane and his pass to Shamar Johnson underneath was stolen as the game ended. Brown gave the Lions a 50-48 lead with five minutes remaining before Kobre scored the next eight points to put Pacific back on top. Brown scored five points and Buay Tuach three in an 8-2 run to tie it at 58-all with 1:26 left. Kobre made four 3-pointers for the Tigers (4-11, 3-3 West Coast), who had nine treys on 21 attempts. Sami Eleraky added 11 points. Brown finished with 15 points for the Lions (7-9, 0-5). David Humphries added 12 points and Tauch 10.
